# Agent intent board

Agents in this repo share a lightweight intent board at
`.cursor/agent-intents/BOARD.md` to avoid file collisions when multiple agents
(or agent + user) work in parallel.

## Before starting work

1. Read `.cursor/agent-intents/BOARD.md`.
2. If another agent has an `active` intent that overlaps your planned files,
   narrow your scope or ask the user before proceeding.
3. Add your own intent entry with status `active` and the files you plan to
   touch.

## While working

- If your scope changes (new files, dropped files), update your entry.
- If you finish a sub-task and want to hand off, change status to `done` and
  note what remains.

## When done

- Set your intent to `done` or remove it entirely.
- If the board has stale entries (status `done` or older than the current
  session), you may clean them up.

## Entry format

```markdown
## <short title>
- **Agent:** <name or id>
- **Status:** planned | active | done
- **Touching:** comma-separated file/folder paths
- **Avoiding:** paths you will not edit
- **Depends on:** (none) or another intent title
- **Notes:** one-liner
```

## Rules

- Never remove another agent's `active` entry.
- Prefer narrow `Touching` lists over broad folder claims.
- The board is local session state — not committed to git.
- When in doubt about overlap, ask the user rather than guessing.
